│                                                                                        │
│ -------------------- BEGIN --------------------                                        │
│ 1. Understanding the Issue:                                                            │
│ The crash occurs in VectorCombine::foldShuffleToIdentity due to an invalid cast to     │
│ FixedVectorType. Specifically, the code uses                                           │
│ cast<FixedVectorType>(FrontU->get()->getType()) at line ~1954 without verifying that   │
│ FrontU's type is a vector. If FrontU refers to a non-vector value (e.g., scalar or     │
│ other non-FixedVectorType), the cast assertion fails, resulting in SIGABRT.            │
│                                                                                        │
│ 2. Analyzing opt's Log:                                                                │
│ The backtrace shows the failure at VectorCombine.cpp:1954 inside                       │
│ foldShuffleToIdentity. The initial checks in foldShuffleToIdentity ensure I is a       │
│ FixedVectorType and has uses, but later the identity check assumes all tracked lanes   │
│ refer to a vector value of the same element count as the destination. The reproducer   │
│ includes a shuffle chain with poison/undef lanes, and an intrinsic call with operand   │
│ bundle; lookThroughShuffles can return an InstLane where the Use points to a           │
│ non-vector value. The debug-only log doesn't print, but the assertion location         │
│ provides precise context.                                                              │
│                                                                                        │
│ 3. Root Cause Analysis:                                                                │
│ In the identity-detection block:                                                       │
│   if (FrontLane == 0 &&                                                                │
│ cast<FixedVectorType>(FrontU->get()->getType())->getNumElements() ==                   │
│ Ty->getNumElements() && ...)                                                           │
│ The code assumes FrontU->get()->getType() is a FixedVectorType. However, due to the    │
│ shuffles with poison/undef and the operand bundle path, lookThroughShuffles may yield  │
│ a Use of a non-vector, causing cast<> to assert. This is consistent with earlier       │
│ protective coding in this file where dyn_cast is used before accessing vector          │
│ properties (see lines 1922, 2028, 2029, 2151, 2155). Therefore, the identity check     │
│ must guard the type with dyn_cast and bail out if it's not a vector.                   │
│                                                                                        │
│ 4. Proposed Edit Point(s):                                                             │
│ Edit llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/VectorCombine.cpp lines 1952-1960 to add a type     │
│ guard before the cast, transforming the identity check to safely handle non-vector     │
│ inputs.                                                                                │
│                                                                                        │
│ Proposed change:                                                                       │
│ - Wrap the identity-check block with a dyn_cast to FixedVectorType and early-return    │
│ false if FrontU's type is not a FixedVectorType.                                       │
│                                                                                        │
│ Concretely:                                                                            │
│ Replace the block starting at line 1952 with:                                          │
│   // Look for an identity value.                                                       │
│   if (FrontLane == 0) {                                                                │
│     auto *FrontTy = dyn_cast<FixedVectorType>(FrontU->get()->getType());               │
│     if (!FrontTy)                                                                      │
│       return false;                                                                    │
│     if (FrontTy->getNumElements() == Ty->getNumElements() &&                           │
│         all_of(drop_begin(enumerate(Item)), [IsEquiv, Item](const auto &E) {           │
│           Value *FrontV = Item.front().first->get();                                   │
│           return !E.value().first || (IsEquiv(E.value().first->get(), FrontV) &&       │
│                                       E.value().second == (int)E.index());             │
│         })) {                                                                          │
│       IdentityLeafs.insert(FrontU);                                                    │
│       continue;                                                                        │
│     }                                                                                  │
│   }                                                                                    │
│                                                                                        │
│ This preserves the original logic but avoids the unsafe cast.                          │
│                                                                                        │
│ 5. Conclusion:                                                                         │
│ By guarding the cast with dyn_cast and bailing out when FrontU is not a vector, we     │
│ prevent the assertion from firing and keep foldShuffleToIdentity robust when           │
│ encountering non-vector uses returned by lookThroughShuffles. The fix aligns with the  │
│ defensive coding style used elsewhere in VectorCombine and should eliminate the crash  │
│ for the provided reproducer without altering intended optimizations.                   │
